Hyperemesis gravidarum is a severe form of morning sickness suffered by 10,000 women a year in the UK . 
  Children exposed to the condition are more likely to have language and speech delays and attention disorders . 
  The Duchess of Cambridge suffered the condition during both her pregnancies . 
  Researchers at UCLA found the condition triples the risk of developmental problems compared with women with normal nausea and vomiting . 
 